<1ST_LINE>r a AM-TysonDivorce     10-10 0170</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Tyson Divorce,0174</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Fighter's Wife Fires Celebrity Divorce Lawyer</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Robin Givens, who last week hired
celebrity divorce lawyer Marvin Mitchelson to oversee the breakup
of her marriage to heavyweight boxing champion Mike Tyson, changed
lawyers on Monday.
   The new attorney, Raoul Felder of New York City, said he would
like to negotiate a settlement.
   Felder said Miss Givens loves the millionaire prizefighter, whom
she accused of beating her and threatening to kill her, but said
there appears no chance to save the eight-month marriage.
   Felder said the case filed Friday in Los Angeles Superior Court
would be handled by one of his West Coast associates rather than by
Mitchelson.
   ``I don't like to say `fired,'' Felder said in a telephone
interview from New York. ``She severed her relationship (with
Mitchelson) and hired me.''
   Mitchelson, who established a live-in companion's right to
alimony-type payments in the celebrated ``palimony'' case against
actor Lee Marvin, refused to comment on reports of his firing,
referring questions to Felder.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
