<FILEID>AP-NR-10-10-88 2327EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i AM-DiscoStampede     10-10 0181</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Disco Stampede,0184</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Six Black Women Killed in South Africa When Crowd Stampedes Disco</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Six young black women were
killed and 17 people were injured Monday evening when a crowd
stampeded the front doors of a disco at an amusment park on the
edge of Soweto, police said.
   Police spokesman Lt. Col. Frans Malherbe said the huge Naledi
Disco at the Shareworld recreation center was less than half-full
when people trying to leave and those trying to enter began pushing
one another at the single door that served as both an entrance and
an exit.
   All the victims were trampled in the doorway, Malherbe said.
   Monday was a public holiday in South Africa and many of the
people at the disco had been drinking heavily, witnesses said.
   They said that at the time of the incident, a large number of
people were arriving at the disco from an all-day rock concert
nearby.
   Shareworld is near Soweto, the main black township outside
Johannesburg. The park is open to all races, although the crowds
are overwhelmingly black.
</TEXT>
