<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Hirohito     10-10 0163</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Hirohito,0169</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ailing Emperor Hirohito Remains In Stable Condition</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Emperor Hirohito, ailing since Sept. 19, remained
in stable condition for the sixth day today, the Imperial Household
Agency said.
   The 87-year-old emperor's fever stood at 99 degrees as of 9:00
a.m., unchanged from Monday morning, according to Kenji Maeda, a
palace spokesman.
   The emperor's normal temperature is about 95.9 degrees.
   Hirohito has been confined to his bed since he vomited a large
amount of blood three weeks ago.
   Since last Thursday he has discharged no blood, but he received
a transfusion of 0.42 pints Monday afternoon, bringing the total
amount of blood he has received in the past three weeks to 13.82
pints.
   Palace doctors, including Akira Takagi, have said they could not
determine whether the internal bleeding has completely stopped,
although no discharge of blood has been detected recently.
   News reports have said the emperor has pancreatic cancer, but
palace officials have neither confirmed nor denied the reports.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
