<1ST_LINE>r a PM-WeddingNightScuffle     10-10 0247</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Wedding Night Scuffle,0253</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Couple Arrested On Wedding Night</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LORAIN, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A newlywed couple was jailed for a drunken
brawl less than 10 hours after they exchanged vows, authorities
said.
   Roger McGee, 28, was released from jail Monday after pleading no
contest to resisting arrest merged with charges of disorderly
conduct and disorderly conduct while intoxicated stemming from
early Sunday's fight with his 19-year-old bride, Tamara Lynn McGee.
   The couple exchanged vows Saturday afternoon and nearly 10 hours
later, police were called to their home on a report that Mrs. McGee
had been assaulted.
   Police arrived to find McGee fighting with Miles Burch, 28, who
told authorities he was trying to help Mrs. McGee. But when police
tried to break up the fight, husband and wife fought with officers
and both had to be handcuffed, said patrolman Raymond West. Once
McGee was in the cruiser, he tried to kick out its rear window,
police said.
   Mrs. McGee was charged with resisting arrest and disorderly
conduct while intoxicated and released Sunday on $700 bond, said
Cindy Paysor, a municipal court clerk.
   Judge V. Paul Timko sentenced McGee to 10 days in jail and
ordered him to pay $250 and court costs, but suspended the jail
time and all but $50 of the fine and court costs, Ms. Paysor said.
   The bride, reached by telephone at her home Monday, declined to
comment.
   Burch was released on $50 bond and pleaded innocent to charges
including disorderly conduct.
</TEXT>
