<HEAD>Plane Hits Terminal Building, Three Passengers Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Indonesian jetliner hit the terminal
building while parking at Bangkok's airport, slightly injuring
three passengers aboard, airport officials said today.
   The Boeing 747's nose and wing, and a few windows of the
building were damaged in the accident Sunday night, said a
spokeswoman of the Airports Authority of Thailand.
   Spokeswoman Nantana Neeyatan said the mishap occured as the
Garuda Indonesia jet was trying to line up with the tube that
allows passengers to walk from the plane to the terminal.
   Three of the 290 passengers aboard suffered slight head
injuries, she said.
   Flight No. 880 arrived from Jakarta, Indonesia's capital, and
from Bangkok was headed to Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates.
Passengers were transferred to other flights.
