<TEXT>
   Actors Michael J. Fox, Al Pacino, Donald
Sutherland, Don Ameche, Robert Prosky and Kevin Bacon are the
headliners for a single performance tonight of David Mamet's new
play, ``Sketches of War.''
   ``It's one act, 25 minutes long,'' Manet said in a Boston Sunday
Globe interview. ``It's a play I wrote a while ago, after I went to
a Soldier of Fortune convention for Esquire. That's where it's
set.''
   The performance at the Colonial Theater is a benefit for
Boston's Vietnam Veterans Workshop.
