<1ST_LINE>r a PM-Chicago-BlackUnity     10-10 0310</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Chicago-Black Unity,0317</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Chicago Black Leaders Divided On Support For Mayoral Candidates</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Black leaders were unable to unite this weekend
in support of a mayoral candidate, and the keynoter at the session
said he fears the community is on the verge of ``political
fratricide.''
   Delegates at Saturday's meeting of black community leaders split
their support between two contenders, Aldermen Danny Davis and
Timothy Evans, while all but snubbing the incumbent.
   Davis garnered 24 votes from the delegates representing black
organizations and Evans got 23. Mayor Eugene Sawyer, a black who
was appointed to fill the vacancy created by the death of Harold
Washington last November, got just six votes.
   Two whites, former Park District president Edmund Kelly and
Lawrence Bloom, are also in the Democratic race. No Republican has
announced for the race.
   ``We are about to commit political fratricide and not have any
political power in this town anymore,'' said attorney Lewis Myer
Jr., the keynote speaker at the meeting.
   ``Unless we have unity we might as well hang it up today,'' said
the Rev. Willie Barrow, leader of Operation PUSH, the Chicago-based
civil rights organization founded by the Rev. Jesse Jackson.
   More than 100 other black groups that were invited to take part
in the meeting either abstained or did not send representatives.
None of the mayoral candidates attended.
   The vote came at the second meeting designed to unify the black
community behind a single candidate.
   Sawyer was appointed mayor by a sharply divided city council
following the death of Washington, the city's first black mayor.
   A Cook County judge set an April 1989 election to fill the
remaining two years of Washington's four-year term. Primaries will
be held in February. Allies of Sawyer, arguing for a 1991 election,
have asked the Illinois Supreme Court to overturn the judge's
ruling. A decision is pending.
</TEXT>
