<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Botswana-US     10-10 0108</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Botswana-US,0109</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Botswana's Ambassador To U.S. Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Serara Ketlogetswe, Botswana's
ambassador to the United States, has died at a hospital in the
capital of Gaborone, the Botswana Press Agency reported today. He
was 68.
   Ketlogetswe was flown to Gaborone on Oct. 1 after American
doctors advised him he should return home, said the agency, quoting
unidentified foreign affairs officials in Botswana. The news agency
did not say when Ketlogetswe died, or give the cause of death.
   Ketlogetswe had been ambassador to the United States for three
years. Prior to that, he served as mayor of Gaborone and a member
of the Cabinet.
