<HEAD>Soviet Pacific Fleet Begins Naval Exercise in Sea of Japan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Japanese anti-submarine patrol plane saw two
Soviet missile destroyers sailing northward in the Sea of Japan on
Monday, indicating the Soviet Pacific Fleet has begun its fall
naval exercise, a Defense Agency spokesman said.
   The ``Udaloy''-class destroyers were seen about 120 miles west
of the tip of Shakotan Peninsula on Hokkaido, Japan's northernmost
main island, said Lt. Cmdr. Yutaka Nojima, the agency spokesman.
   OnSunday, five Soviet warships were seen by a Japanese patrol
plane off nearby Rebun Island, Nojima said.
   Last year, the Soviet Union mobilized more than 20 military
vessels in its fall exercise, conducted for about a week, he said.
