<DOCNO> AP881010-0140 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-10-10-88 1941EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Papandreou 1stLd-Writethru a0594 10-10 0229</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Papandreou, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0594,0231</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Greek Leader Leaves Hospital 10 Days After Heart Surgery</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS grafs 3-5 pvs `Dimitre Liani... to Greece.' with 5 grafs
to DELETE incorrect reference to announcement of marriage plans and
ADD quotes from spokesman.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Greek Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou,
recovering from heart surgery, left the hospital Monday with his
girlfriend at his side and went to a hotel for further
convalescence.
   Papandreou, 69, underwent an operation to replace a heart valve
10 days ago at Harefield Hospital.
   Dimitre Liani, who has been a frequent visitor at the hospital,
accompanied Papandreou as he left the hospital. Her presence has
prompted widespread speculation that the prime minister planned to
end his 37-year marriage and marry Mrs. Liani, 34.
   The Greek Embassy said he will spend about 10 days at the
Grosvenor House Hotel before returning to Greece.
   ``He has made a speedy recovery from his operation and has been
allowed out of hospital in a very fast time,'' said Papandreou's
spokesman, Tilemacos Chytiris.
   ``He must go back there twice for check-ups before he returns to
Greece,'' Chytiris said. ``He has an office in the hotel and will
be in contact with the Greek government. He can also go out for
walks.''
   ``The doctors at Harefield have said he is very well and he will
get better very soon,'' the spokesman said.
