<HEAD>Truck Driver Released on Bond</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARROLLTON, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man charged with 27 counts of murder in
a May 14 bus crash was released from jail Monday, officials said.
   Larry W. Mahoney, 35, of Worthville, posted $540,000 bond at the
Carroll Circuit Court Monday night, said clerk William Wheeler.
   The fiery crash occurred as a church bus was returning from an
outing at an amusement park. The bus was struck head-on by a pickup
truck traveling the wrong way and driven by Mahoney, police said.
   Mahoney is charged with 27 counts of murder, 13 counts of
first-degree assault, 44 counts of first-degree wanton endangerment
and one count of drunken driving.
   His trial is scheduled to begin Jan. 9.
