<1ST_LINE>u a AM-FireDeaths     10-10 0192</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Fire Deaths,0198</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Three Killed in Apartment Fire Believed Started by Electrical
Problem</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire swept through the top two floors of an
apartment building Monday, killing three people and injuring five
others, an official said.
   Witnesses told firefighters that lights in the building
flickered just minutes before the fire broke out, prompting
speculation an electrical problem or an overloaded circuit caused
the fire, said Fire Department spokesman Frank Szwedo.
   ``We won't know for sure until the investigators have gone over
the place,'' he said. ``But these buildings are pretty old.''
   Rescue efforts were hampered by burglar bars over the windows
and apartment doors, he said.
   The Cook County medical examiner's office said three adults were
killed but did not release further information.
   One woman suffered severe burns over her face and body and was
being treated at a hospital, officials said.
   Leon Collins, father of two children injured in the fire, and
Billy Hibbler, both about 20, were being treated for smoke
inhalation. Collins also was treated for burns along the face and
neck.
   Two children were hospitalized for burns and were listed in fair
and stable conditions.
</TEXT>
