<HEAD>Brothers Die in House Fire</HEAD>
<NOTE>With LaserPhoto ROC2</NOTE>
<DATELINE>ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two young brothers were killed in a house
fire Monday, their bodies found ``cuddled in a corner,''
firefighters said.
   A 1-year-old boy was seriously injured.
   The brothers, Gregory, 4, and Peter Acevedo, 3, were found in a
bedroom adjacent to the kitchen where the fire apparently started,
said deputy fire chief Ernest Miller.
   Daniel Amador, the 1-year-old, was found on the floor of another
bedroom suffering from smoke inhalation. He was listed in ``guarded
condition'' at Strong Memorial Hospital, a spokesman said.
   Firefighters said the boys' stepfather was home when the fire
started.
   The family moved to the United States from Puerto Rico about two
years, a family member said.
   The fire was under investigation.
