<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   George Bush and Michael Dukakis focused on strategy and studied
for their second presidential debate as state polls across the
nation indicated that the Republican nominee is solidifying his
lead over the Democratic challenger.
   The vice president spent several hours at his Washington, D.C.,
