<HEAD>U.S. Bond Market Closed in Observance of Columbus Day</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government bond market was closed Monday in
observance of the Columbus Day holiday, but prices of corporate
bonds edged higher.
   Moody's Investment Grade Corporate Bond Index, which measures
price movements on 80 corporate bonds with maturities of five years
or longer, rose 0.23 to finish at 295.77.
   The cash market for Treasury bonds and notes was closed,
however, along with banks and the Federal Reserve, in observance of
Columbus Day.
