third-quarter earnings, rose [ to 44[
   Among other actively traded blue chips, American Telephone &
Telegraph gained { to 27; American Express 1\ to 30; McDonald's 1]
to 51, and International Business Machines [ to 116[.
   Precious metals stocks chalked up broad gains as the price of
gold rallied $5.40 an ounce to $408.60 on the Commodity Exchange in
New York, responding in part to higher oil prices.
   ASA Ltd. picked up } to 39{; Newmont Gold 2 to 35~; Battle
Mountain Gold ~ to 15}, and Freeport-McMoRan Gold | to 13\.
   Major oil issues were mixed with fractional price changes.
   Time Inc., which has been caught up lately in speculation about
a possible buyout or other deal, was up 3 at 120{.
   As measured by Wilshire Associates' index of more than 5,000
actively traded stocks, the market increased $1.02 billion, or 0.04
percent, in value.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks edged
up .15 to 156.95.
