<2ND_LINE>BC-Continental Management,0250</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Continental Airlines Restructures Senior Management</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Continental Airlines has named two executives to
new positions in charge of marketing and finance and planning, the
airline's president announced Monday.
   Continental President Martin R. Shugrue said John W. Nelson
would serve as vice president in charge of marketing and Mickey
Foret will serve as executive vice president of finance and
planning.
   Nelson will be responsible for all of Houston-based
Continental's marketing activities, including advertising, sales,
marketing programs, pricing, reservations and customer relations,
Shugrue said.
   Nelson joined Continental from Eastern Airlines, where during
the last 20 years held several vice president positions in charge
of sales, personnel, revenue accounting, southern region and
Florida-Bahamas. Most recently, he was senior vice president in
charge of marketing.
   Eastern and Continental are owned by Texas Air Corp.
   Foret's new responsibilities include strategic planning, airline
planning and scheduling, treasury, financial planning and control,
accounting, properties and facilities, purchasing and management
information systems.
   Foret joined Texas International Airlines in 1974 and held
positions of assistant treasurer and vice president in charge of
financial services among others in the finance department.
   He was named finance vice preident and treasurer of Continental
following the merger of Texas International and Continental in
1982, and was promoted to vice president of finance and chief
financial officer in 1984. In October 1986, he joined Miami-based
Eastern and earlier this year was named senior vice president of
Houston-based Texas Air.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
